Join the EvacServices team, where we prioritize fostering a workplace culture
that values our people, embraces diversity, and nurtures career growth. We
assist buildings and businesses in meeting their emergency training and
compliance requirements. We aim to give our customers peace of mind in their
emergency planning efforts.

In this newly created role of Business System Administrator, you will play a
pivotal role in understanding and addressing business challenges through
system and process enhancements, offering innovative solutions across various
departments.

Your responsibilities will span a diverse range of projects, including
business analysis, process design, systems administration project management,
IT asset management, corporate reporting, and business partnering.

Key Responsibilities:

  * Conduct end-to-end analysis, design, programming, testing, training, implementation, monitoring, and improvement of systems and processes. 
  * Assist in planning, testing, and executing system upgrades. 
  * Provide technical support for managed systems. 
  * Demonstrate strong analytical and reporting capabilities. 
  * Engage with a wide array of business and technical stakeholders. 
  * Collaborate with the organization to deliver simple and time-critical solutions. 
  * Handle IT tasks as required, including technology and telephony administration. 
  * Prepare and maintain technical and user documentation. 
  * Oversee database administration across the organization. 

Qualifications and Requirements:

  * Tertiary qualification or equivalent experience. 
  * Substantial experience in a Business Systems Administrator role. 
  * Proficiency in workflow and automation development. 
  * Strong data analytics and sustainable solution design skills. 
  * Experience with CRM/ERP systems. 
  * Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities. 
  * Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills. 
  * Capability to work independently and collaboratively within a team. 
  * Developer / Programmers with extensive experience with data analysis tools like SQL. 
  * Familiarity with Airtable, PHP, and emerging web development frameworks. 

Desirable Skills:

  * Experience with project management methodologies such as Agile or Prince. 
  * Familiarity with workflow systems like Airtable. 
  * Knowledge of AI and machine learning concepts. 

We offer a competitive salary package along with the opportunity to be part of
a dedicated team within the fire safety and compliance industry. Join us by
submitting your resume and cover letter highlighting why this role resonates
with you. Apply now!

